	     THE Mountain Rise SAPS is asking the community to assist with finding a missing person, Vanessa Pillay (34).  Pillay is from Krishnan Road, Northdale and was last seen on Monday, July 24, after she told her brother she was taking her child to the child’s father.  Mountain Rise SAPS spokesperson, Captain Gay Ebrahim said Pillay left the child with her husband, but was never seen again.  Pillay has brown and black hair and brown eyes.  Anyone with the information of her whereabouts is asked to contact Mountain Rise SAPS on 033 387 9600 or our Crime Stop number on 08600 10111. - Supplied. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  